 key moral panics have played in social processes, arguing forcefully against the political abuse of sex panics and for the need to defend full sexual and reproductive rights.Contributors: Cathy J. Cohen, Diane DiMauro, Gary W. Dowsett, Janice M. Irvine, Carole Joffe, and Saskia Eleonora Wieringa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEthical absolutismxHistory. 0aGay rightszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aGender identityzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSexual minoritieszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSexual rightszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aAIDS.  aThese.  acase.  acontroversies.  adown.  aeducation.  aessays.  afocus.  afrom.  aheart.  aillustrate.  alow.  amany.  apolitical.  arace.  aranging.  asexuality.  astudies.1 aCohen, Cathy J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowsett, Gary W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerdt, Gilbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerdt, Gilbert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIrvine, Janice M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoffe, Carole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWieringa, Saskia Eleonora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 adi Mauro, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081473722440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814790847.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814790847423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814790847/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York Un